    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<h1>gossip, gossips, talk nonsense</h1><h2>Definition:</h2><p>The term “gossip” refers to talking to people about someone else’s personal affairs, usually in a negative and unproductive way. Often what is talked about has not been confirmed as true.</p><ul><li><p>The Bible says that spreading negative information about people is wrong. Gossip and slander are examples of this kind of negative speech.</p></li><li><p>Gossip is harmful to the person being spoken about because it often hurts someone’s relationships with other people.</p></li></ul><p>(See also: <span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"26244\" data-resourceType=\"UWTranslationWords\">slander</span>)</p><h2>Bible References:</h2><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:13\">1 Timothy 5:13</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:20\">2 Corinthians 12:20</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:15-Lev19:16\">Leviticus 19:15–16</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:28\">Proverbs 16:28</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:29-Rom1:31\">Romans 1:29–31</a></p></li></ul><h2>Word Data:</h2><ul><li><p>Strong’s: H5372, G26360, G53970</p></li></ul>",
